Notice No. 01-310

September 21, 2001


TO:

All NYMEX Division Members

All NYMEX Division Commodity Managers

All NYMEX Division Clearing Members


FROM:

J. Robert Collins, Jr., President


RE:

Deadlines for EFPs and Notice of Intention to Deliver and Accept for the October 2001 Crude Oil Futures


        The deadline for submission of EFPs in the October 2001 Crude Oil Future has been extended to 12:00 P.M. Monday, September 24, 2001.  The deadline for submission of Notices of Intention to Deliver and Accept by clearing members for the October 2001 Crude Oil Futures contract has been extended until 1:00 P.M. on Monday, September 24, 2001.


Clearing members may submit Notices of Intention to Deliver or Accept prior to the revised deadline as they are available and may amend submissions until the Monday 1:00 P.M. requirement.


                All floor members and their clerks, as well as clearing members, are requested to dedicate all resources to resolve any open trade discrepancies in order to facilitate the submission of the required information.


